What are the differences between Native IDs and IDs issued by fractional or centralized currencies in terms of launching currencies and their other capabilities on the Verus platform?

On the Verus platform, there are two types of IDs: Native IDs and IDs issued by fractional or centralized currencies. Native IDs, which are registered directly from a blockchain as the name parent, have the ability to launch currencies on that blockchain. In fact, if the Native ID is on the Verus blockchain, it can even launch independent blockchains. 

On the other hand, IDs issued by fractional or centralized currencies cannot launch currencies. However, they are still valuable as revocation and recovery IDs for all other VerusIDs. They can also be used for personalized on-chain and cross-chain addresses with various features such as identity, NFTs, proofs, brands, contract binding, on-chain marketplace trading, or login. Additionally, they have the ability to cross-prove common ownership with other IDs.

There is an exception to this rule, which is that *.veth gateway IDs will be available for decentralized registration from the Ethereum bridge converter. These IDs will be able to create Ethereum mapped currencies. The registration of.veth IDs will be priced to prevent misuse and support bridge liquidity.

In summary, Native IDs have more capabilities, including launching currencies and independent blockchains, while IDs issued by fractional or centralized currencies have more limited capabilities, but are still valuable for other purposes.

While Native IDs, those registered directly from a blockchain as the name parent, will be able to launch currencies on that blockchain, and if on Verus, actual independent blockchains, IDs issued by fractional or centralized currencies cannot launch currencies, but will still be valuable as revocation and recovery IDs for all other VerusIDs as well as for personalized on-chain and cross-chain addresses with all identity and NFT features, for proofs, for brands, contract binding, on-chain marketplace trading, or login, and will have the ability to cross-prove common ownership with other IDs as well.The exception to non-native IDs creating currencies, is that *.veth gateway IDs will be available for decentralized registration from the Ethereum bridge converter and will be able to create Ethereum mapped currencies.
